{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6868ace2-d990-48f1-8a6a-11888b788f44","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_KJeUFBfFLn5PRS3M25O5cb","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-da2fd9c2275d4dd9871b214cfd30b712/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-da2fd9c2275d4dd9871b214cfd30b712/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"729fe12f-bbdf-4926-b3be-eac9d2880856","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n```xml\n<Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n<Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n```\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain` which is defined in `Domain.fs`. This means `Services.fs` is trying to use types that haven't been compiled yet.\n\nThe fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":460,"requestId":"042A:246CF2:C63449:E4397E:69F2A775"},"id":"37ab3502-91d4-4cc5-b311-796b0989f0a9","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:51:09.823Z","parentId":"7b9c6143-e99a-4060-9a19-97056d122189"}
